The Olympic flame does not illuminate all events equally.
Away from the center, in the shadows, are sports that are not universally recognized: air rifle shooting, archery, badminton, taekwondo.
The frog will always be with us, and may it be for a long time.
But to name my personal favorite, I'd like to point out the hidden magic of the trampoline.
Although trampolining has been recognized as an Olympic event since its introduction at the Sydney Games in 2000, very few people I've interviewed in the 16 years since have realized that it's an Olympic sport.
It could be regional ignorance.
The United States, although sending athletes to compete, has never won a medal in trampolining and did not have a competitor reach the finals until 2012.
