There are two types of leg artery systems:
The deep vein system in the leg is the main route that carries dirty blood to the lungs and collects the main dirty blood in the leg.
These are called the deep femoral vein and the superficial femoral vein.
Problems in these blood vessels are less common, and in these cases, the vessels cannot be closed and medications are used to keep them open.
