This system is made up of two large and two small vessels called saphenous veins.
Deficiency and varicose veins can develop in all four of these veins.
The arteries that are used in heart surgery are superficial arteries called the great saphenous vein.
The absence of these vessels does no harm to the body, and therefore they can be used in heart surgery.
But for these vessels to be used in heart surgery, they need to be healthy.
Because the heart is a very important organ.
Removing the vessels by surgery or burning them with a laser also reduces the workload on the deep veins and makes the leg healthier.
A common misconception is that even if you're an heir, your blood vessels can be used as a backup.
The varicose vein is never, ever used in heart surgery!
